description:
&lt;p&gt;*Trainee Mammographers welcome to apply*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for two enthusiastic qualified or trainee Mammographers to join our team. We will accept applications from trained mammographers or applications from Radiographers willing to train in Mammography and take on the PG Cert in Mammography.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The North Lancashire and South Cumbria Breast Screening Service invites around 125,000 women every three years for screening. The service has two mobile units, as well as three static sites at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Royal Lancaster Infirmary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Westmorland General Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Furness General Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst the role would be based at Royal Lancaster Infirmary, there would be a requirement to work cross-bay to meet the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the current national guidance on Health Promotion within Breast Screening, this opportunity is open to female applicants only. This provision applies under the Equality Act 2010 (and an equality impact assessment has been completed).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGeorgia ArgentJob titleHead of Breast ScreeningEmail addressGeorgia.Argent@mbht.nhs.ukTelephone number01524519455Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Georgia Argent - Head of Department - Georgia.argent@mbht.nhs.uk / 01524 519455&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leanne Coulson - Deputy Head of Department - Leanne.coulson@mbht.nhs.uk / 01524519455&lt;/p&gt;
